Attractions.description: Open daily 8am-sunset. This utopian community of 200 which believed the entire universe existed within a giant, hollow sphere relocated from New York to Florida in 1894. The Koreshans built and operated a printing facility, boat works, cement works, sawmill, bakery, store and hostelry. Education, science and art also helped shape their community. After their leader's death in 1908, membership declined. In 1961, the remaining members deeded 305 acres of their land to the state of Florida as a park and memorial. The Koreshan Unity Settlement Historic District is on the National Register of Historic Places. Guided tours available.

Restaurants.description: In April of 2008, Angelina’s Ristorante opened its doors in Bonita Springs, Florida, and ushered in guests to a Mediterranean oasis of delicious food, fine wines, and the promise of incomparable experiences. More than a decade later, we are now one of Southwest Florida’s most awarded restaurants and we are still just as passionate about providing Unmatched Fine Italian in all aspects. Your unmatched experience begins at the door with our friendly, complimentary valet. While you’re guided to your table, you'll hear live piano music drifting through the dining rooms and take in the spectacular sight that is our unique 30-foot refrigerated wine tower containing more than 4,000 bottles from around the world. Our meticulously trained service staff will then wine, dine, and dazzle you with traditional Italian hospitality. When your evening comes to an end, we hope you are departing with delightful, unmatched memories and plans to come and see us again soon.

Restaurants.description: Naples Flatbread started the flatbread craze back in 2009--with bold, sensual flavor combinations served on a house made crust (regular and cauliflower) and cooked in a fiery hearth oven. The menu is dynamic--with items like Neapolitan pizza, gourmet baked pastas, flatbread encrusted Wagyu burgers, and a variety of mouth-watering gourmet mac and cheese'.
